<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Develop Small Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian government is
making efforts geared toward the development of small private
enterprises, an official from the Ministry of Trade and Industry
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government has formulated and adopted a national
strategy for promoting the development of small enterprises, which
lays out a systematic approach to the development of the sector,
said Jemil Mohammed, the official with the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The government has also mobilized the assistance of its
development partners to enhance the development of small
enterprises, the Ethiopian News Agency quoted Mohammed as saying.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the governments of Ethiopia and Germany
have launched the Ethio-German small enterprises development
program to improve the performance of the existing enterprises and
create new ones.
</P>
<P>
Some regional administrations are also in the process of
providing the necessary legal framework for the establishment of
regional small enterprises development agencies, he added.
</P>
<P>
There are currently about 600,000 handicraftsmen and small
private enterprises which provide over 700,000 jobs in the Horn of
Africa country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
