<HEADLINE> China Favors Political Solution to Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- China Monday said that it
favors a political solution to the question of Kosovo, a Serbian
province, and opposes imposing any solution on the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia (FRY).
</P>
<P>
The statement was made by Qin Huasun, Chinese permanent
representative to the United Nations, as he was speaking to
reporters here after a closed-door Security Council session on the
current situation in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"We are deeply concerned over the deterioration of the
situation in the Balkan region caused by the continued NATO
military strikes against the FRY," Qin said. "We are in favor of a
political solution of the question of Kosovo, the FRY."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese ambassador also called for an immediate end to the
ongoing NATO air strikes on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Qin's statement came as several countries had put forward
several proposals on how to solve the question of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that any political solution should be based on two
principles, namely faithful respect for and maintenance of the
sovereignty and territorial integrity of the FRY, and protection
of the legitimate rights of all ethnic groups in Kosovo, the FRY,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"In this regard, it is very important to seek the consent of
the government of the FRY when any plan is to be discussed," he
said. "We are against imposing any solution on the FRY. As for
now, it is a matter of priority for NATO to cease immediately its
military action against the FRY."
</P>
<P>
NATO entered its fourth week in bombing Yugoslavia, a sovereign
and independent member of the U.N. family and creating a large
exodus of refugees and a serious humanitarian crisis in the
Serbian province.
</P>
<P>
NATO, without the authorization of the U.N. Security Council,
began the air strikes on March 24, violating the U.N. Charter and
international law. Many peace-loving countries have called for an
immediate end to NATO's illegal military action. 
</P>
</TEXT>
