<HEADLINE> Botswana Trade Deficit Nearly Seven Million U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Botswana Monday
estimated a trade deficit of 30 million Pula (about 6.94 million
U.S. dollars) for the country in 1998, the first since 1982.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association quoted the bank as saying that
the current account deficit in Botswana was about 375 million Pula
(about 86.8 million dollars).
</P>
