<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC Meets on Employment of National Manpower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) Consultative Committee began a meeting here Monday on the
employment of national manpower and facilitating their movement
among member states.
</P>
<P>
The meeting came in implementing recommendations of the
previous GCC summit on expanding the employment of GCC nationals
and giving them equal employment rights in member countries, said
Mohammed Eid Al Muraikhi, chairman of the committee.
</P>
<P>
The initiative to give GCC nationals equal employment rights
in member states was a major part of the agenda for the 19th GCC
summit which took place here last November.
</P>
<P>
The GCC comprises Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, Bahrain, Oman
and the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
Jamil Hujailan, secretary general of the GCC, said at the
meeting that as a regional organization, the GCC was established
on the basis of social, economic and cultural agreement among its
member countries.
</P>
<P>
The GCC economic agreement has created a free market for the
movement of services, capitals and commodities of the Gulf region,
he said.
</P>
<P>
"It has also created joint economic establishments such as the
Gulf Investment Organization, the Gulf organization for
Industrial Consultations, the Commercial Arbitration Center and
the Gulf Patent Office," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
