<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-19 20:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Arrests Seven Suspected Militants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian prosecutors Monday ordered
the arrest of seven Islamic militant suspects who were extradited
from three Arab countries last week.
</P>
<P>
The arrest finished a legal procedure required before the
suspects can be charged and tried in a state security court.
</P>
<P>
The specific indictments against them are not clear for now but
they were wanted for terrorist acts in the country over the past
15 years, security officials said.
</P>
<P>
They were suspected members of the outlawed group, Jihad, or
Holy War, which assassinated former Egyptian President Anwar Sadat
in 1981.
</P>
<P>
Since their extradition by Kuwait, Yemen and Sudan, the seven
had been detained for interrogation.
</P>
<P>
About 20 suspected Islamic militants have been extradited to
Egypt over the last three months from Arab, European and South
American countries.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's Islamic militants launched an insurgency in 1992 in an
attempt to topple the secular government and install a strict
Islamic rule. More than 1,200 people have been killed in the
insurgency, mostly militants and policemen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
