<HEADLINE> 3 Dead, 13 Missing as Sea Boat Sinks in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The bodies of three
fishermen were recovered from the sea off South Africa's Eastern
Cape coast Monday afternoon, but 13 other crew were still missing
after their boat went down in a raging storm, South African
Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) reported.
</P>
<P>
The rescue operation will not be called off until the first
light of Tuesday morning, according to the SABC, the state
television.
</P>
<P>
The missing boat, fishing for squid, was thought to have gone
down between 4:00 a.m. (0200 GMT) and 8:00 a.m. (0600 GMT) Monday.
 
</P>
