KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwaiti Oil Minister Saud Nasser Al-Sabah said
Monday he was relieved over the present oil price hikes following
the recent output cuts by the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries (OPEC).
</P>
<P>
The prices are improving in the right and desirable direction,
Saud told Kuwait News Agency during the foundation laying ceremony
for a catalyst plant.
</P>
<P>
The average price of OPEC's basket of seven crudes reached
14.83 U.S. dollars per barrel last Thursday. (BC-Kuwait-Oil)
