<HEADLINE> Another Group of Italian Soldiers Arrive in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Italy Monday sent another
contingent of 400 soldiers to Albania to join troops from other
NATO nations called in for carrying out what was called the Allied
Harbor operation.
</P>
<P>
The Italian soldiers arrived in the Albanian port Durres by
freighters, which also carried 120 trucks, an armored personnel
carrier and vehicles for road building.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian news agency ATA said the soldiers will repair
roads and set up new refugee camps.
</P>
<P>
With the new arrivals, the total number of Italian soldiers in
Albania has risen to 1,200.
</P>
<P>
Italy has committed itself to contributing 1,600 soldiers to an
8,000-strong NATO force being deployed to implement the
humanitarian operation.
</P>
<P>
Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani said Monday that the number
of ethnic Albanian refugees from the southern Serbian province of
Kosovo to Albania has reached 400,000.
</P>
<P>
Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli Majko told an European
Commission delegation Monday that the number of Kosovo refugees is
expected to surpass the half million mark in a very short time.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country has tried its best to face with the
emergent situation arising from the ever-growing number of
refugees coming across the border from Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo, along with other parts of Yugoslavia, has been under
continuous and extensive NATO air bombardment since March 24 when
the Western military alliance launched air strikes on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian parliament discussed Monday the refugee problem
and the implementation of a program designed to meet the needs of
the refugees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
