<HEADLINE> Russia Pushing For Peaceful Settlement of Kosovo Issue: Yeltsin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia will continue to seek a
peaceful settlement of the Kosovo issue, even though the country
uncompromisingly opposes NATO's action in Yugoslavia, Russian
President Boris Yeltsin said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with leaders of 19 regions in the Kremlin Palace,
Yeltsin stressed that in the mediation process on the Kosovo issue,
Russia's relations with Western European countries will play a
unique role, the president's press secretary Dmitri Yakushkin said.
</P>
<P>
Russia should not isolate itself from world powers or cut off
relations with them, Yeltsin said. He called for regional leaders
to participate in the peaceful resolution of the Kosovo problem.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his uneasiness over the escalation of anti-Western
and anti-American sentiment in some regions of Russia. 
</P>
