<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNITA Rebels Advancing to Angolan Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Armed rebel forces of the National
Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) are flooding
into northern Angola's Kwanza-sul Province, which is a gate to
capital city Luanda, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Higino Carneiro, governor of the province, said the situation
is " critical".
</P>
<P>
He said UNITA's regular troops and guerrillas who have won some
battles in central Angola, are launching offenses to the province,
inflicting big losses on the part of the government forces.
</P>
<P>
Carneiro did not say how many of his cities and towns are now
under UNITA's control, but he said that all the people in his
province have been mobilized to resist UNITA's attacks.
</P>
<P>
Last weekend a foreign non-governmental organization group,
heading for a humanitarian aid conference, were ambushed by UNITA,
killing all six people on a car, the governor said.
</P>
<P>
Carneiro, also a hard-line general determined to wipe out
UNITA, was assigned to Kwanza-sul at the end of January after a
governmental reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, situation in the neighboring Benge Province, which
has been haunted by UNITA guerrillas, is also intensifying, with
refugee flooding into the Caxito, capital of the province about 40
kms from Luanda.
</P>
<P>
People in the capital can smell a strong sense of war, while
the government is enrolling youths for its troops from every
corner of the city, armed police checking vehicles and pedestrians
on the streets.
</P>
<P>
Situation in central Angola went panic after governmental
troops failed in their fight against UNITA in Andulo City,
headquarters of UNITA. It is reported that UNITA forces captured
a strategically important city of Alto Catumbela in Benguela
Province.
</P>
<P>
But the report has not been confirmed by the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
