<DOCNO> XIE19990420.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Inflation Drops in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's year-on-year
consumer inflation rate was 7.9 percent in March, a sharp decrease
from February's 8. 6 percent, Statistics South Africa announced
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The fall was attributed mainly to a further drop in home loan
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The annual core inflation rate, which excludes mortgage
payments and other volatile items, rose to eight percent in march
from 7.8 percent in February.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fall in the headline consumer inflation rate,
economists Tuesday warned against over-optimism.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association quoted Standard Bank's economic
division as saying that proposed fuel price hikes would have an
adverse effect on the rate.
</P>
<P>
The fuel price is expected to rise by 17 cents (0.028 U.S.
dollars) per liter at the beginning of May owing to oil price
hikes on international markets.
</P>
<P>
"Consumer inflation will be affected once the higher import
cost of oil results in changes in petroleum prices at retail
level," the bank said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
