<HEADLINE> Malaysian Brothers Walk to North Pole </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Brothers Justin and Gerald
Read have become the first Malaysians to walk the last degree to
the North Pole after battling an extreme weather condition,
according to a statement Tuesday by Benson &AMP; Hedges Golden Dreams
which organized the event.
</P>
<P>
The duo reached the Geographic North Pole on April 19, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said Justin, 19, and Gerald, 25, were elated at their
conquest of the earth's polar region and at setting a new
Malaysian record.
</P>
<P>
Justin may have set a new world record as the youngest person
ever to walk the last degree to the Pole, it added.
</P>
<P>
"The final day proved a far greater challenge when the team
battled extreme weather conditions such as gale force winds and
snow," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The last degree entails a 111 km walk in temperatures of
between minus 10 and minus 30 degrees centigrade, among other
things.
</P>
<P>
The team, comprising the brothers, a guide and two film crew
began their walk on April 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
