<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Regulations to Promote Industrialization of Scientific Results (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- New regulations aimed at
encouraging scientific organizations, higher-learning institutes
and their staff to research and develop high technology and speed
up the industrialization of research results have been issued by
the General Office of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Jointly compiled by the Ministry of Science and Technology, the
Ministry of Education and other government organizations the rules
are promulgated under the title Regulations on Promoting the
Industrialization of Scientific And Technological Results.
</P>
<P>
They are divided into three parts and incorporate detailed
principles boosting scientific results, guaranteeing the right of
self-management of high-tech enterprises, and providing a better
environment for the industrialization of high technology.
</P>
<P>
"The older laws, regulations and policies concerning the same
issues are too general to give enough incentive and guidance to
relevant people," Xu Guanhua, vice-minister of Science and
Technology said during an interview with reporters from the Xinhua
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that the new regulations are more detailed and more
feasible than old ones and provide new policies which will guide
scientific organizations, higher-learning institutes and
scientific and technological workers to become involved in the
industrialization of scientific results, and to form more high-
tech enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990420.0095 </DOCNO>
