<DOCNO> XIE19990420.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Regulations to Promote Industrialization of Scientific Results (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The regulations also encourage scientific organizations and
higher-learning institutes to become shareholders of enterprises
through high-tech contributions, and to link up with people from
other circles to establish high-tech enterprises," Xu explained.
</P>
<P>
To further speed up the process, people can choose to
industrialize their research results in accordance with relevant
agreements with their institutes or organizations one year after
the development of the results, according to one of the
regulations.
</P>
<P>
"They also provide a number of detailed principles for
rewarding people who make major contributions to the development
and industrialization of scientific findings," said Xu.
</P>
<P>
He said that scientific employees are allowed to do part-time
jobs or engage in moon-lighting, but only where this concerns the
research, development and industrialization of scientific results.
</P>
<P>
According to another regulation, scientific employees are
allowed to leave their institute for less than two years to do
other research and development work, and will be given equal
opportunity to compete for positions in their original workplaces
when they return.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that the Ministry of Science and Technology will co-
operate with relevant departments on issues concerning real estate,
personnel and taxation to guarantee a smooth implementation of the
regulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
