<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets European Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here today with a
delegation from the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of
Europe led by its president Lord Russell-Johnston.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and Europe, both with a long history, have
the right to be proud of their contribution to human civilization
and progress. He stressed that each country has its own history,
culture, religion and development path. "All these should be
respected," he added.
</P>
<P>
China's NPC and the parliamentary assembly have kept friendly
exchanges in recent years and such exchanges should be
strengthened in the future, Li said, adding that, "Only through
deepening understanding can the cooperation be expanded."
</P>
<P>
Russell-Johnston conveyed his gratitude to the NPC and Li Peng
and briefed his Chinese host on the composition and function of
the Council of Europe and its Parliamentary Assembly.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his appreciation for the efforts made by the
Chinese government to develop the country's economy and improve
the living standards of the people.
</P>
<P>
He told Li that all members in the delegation represent
different political parties from different countries. Even with
different political orientation, he said, all members expressed a
willingness to be friends of China. "Even after only several days
in China, they all had a distinct impression of China's fast-
growing economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Council of Europe, made up of 40 European countries, is the
largest pan-Europe international organization. Its Parliamentary
Assembly is a consultative branch of the council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
