<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scientists Mark 80th Anniversary of May 4 Movement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of well-known Chinese
scientists stressed at today's forum to commemorate the 80th
anniversary of the May 4 Movement that the future of the nation
depends on the fostering of a scientific spirit.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the China Association for Science and Technology (
CAST), the forum was one of the many events planned to mark the
anti-imperialist, anti-feudal, political and cultural movement
which flourished earlier this century.
</P>
<P>
"It aroused Chinese intellectuals, as well as the common people
and imbued in them a fervor for patriotism, science and democracy,
" said Zhou Guangzhao, vice-chairman of the National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
He added that the spirit advocated during the movement has
practical and immediate significance in scientific circles to this
day.
</P>
<P>
The movement also blew away the feudal system and outmoded
concepts which had ruled China for more than two millennia.
Theorists in the enlightenment movement believed that only
democracy and science could save and invigorate China.
</P>
<P>
Patriotism and good academic discipline should be emphasized in
the scientific circle today, said Zhou, who is also the president
of the CAST, and the scientific knowledge, spirit and thoughts
should be spread to the public.
</P>
<P>
Experts attending the forum said that science and technology
has taken deep root in all the fields of economic and social
developments in China 80 years after the May 4 Movement. Meanwhile,
the scientific spirit should enter the social life and become a
standard for the whole society.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the scientific spirit has an important role in
maintaining social stability, promoting economic development,
improving the people's life and in making decisions by the
government.
</P>
<P>
China has initiated the strategy of invigorating the nation
through science and technology, which is a development of late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's theory that science and technology
is the first productive force.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji has emphasized for several times
that the implementation of the strategy will be a major task of
the current government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
