<HEADLINE> British MPs Urge NATO to Stop Bombing in Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Two British Parliament Members (
MPs) on Tuesday condemned NATO's bombing on Yugoslavia and told
the military alliance that the only way to solve the Kosovo crisis
is political negotiation.
</P>
<P>
Alice Mahon, who just came back from a two-day trip to
Yugoslavia, told a press conference held in the House of Commons
on Tuesday morning that NATO's bombing can not solve the problems
in Yugoslavia and would provide more refugees that can never be
back home unless the airstrikes was stopped.
</P>
<P>
"I think what we supposed to be the first humanitarian war
actually created a humanitarian disaster," Mahon said.
</P>
<P>
She said she had the feeling that NATO's bombing forced more
people to stand on the side of Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic, and that unless NATO stops its bombing, the fight would
keep on and there would be no way to end the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav people had the strong feeling that the United States
wanted to take over their country and they would surely fight the
war against NATO, Mahon said.
</P>
<P>
"This is war. It's going to be worse because the Serbs will
fight. They know the Americans want to take over their country,"
Mahon said.
</P>
<P>
"We will fight for our country in every town, every village and
every house and behind every tree. We are not going to give up,"
Mahon said she was repeatedly told by Yugoslavs.
</P>
<P>
"The only hope is to keep pressing all sides to get the United
Nations involved, involve the Russians, try to come out with a
political solution that form the bases of negotiation at the very
least, and not just keep repeating what we tried for months at
Rambouillet. It didn't work," Mahon said.
</P>
<P>
Tam Dalyell, another MP attending the conference, said NATO's
policy in Yugoslavia now is causing more problems in that region
rather than solving it.
</P>
<P>
"This kind of bombing does not make the situation better. It
makes it far, far worse," Dalyell said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
