<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Wu Zuoren Art Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition highlighting the
works of Wu Zuoren, a noted Chinese artist opened at the China Art
Gallery today to mark his 90th birthday.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
and chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
On display are 470 masterpieces, including 152 oil paintings,
80 traditional Chinese paintings and 156 sketches.
</P>
<P>
Wu, born in 1908 in Suzhou City of East China's Jiangsu
Province, studied under the noted artist Xu Beihong and served as
president of the Central Academy of Fine Arts.
</P>
<P>
Wu made important contributions to the theory and practice of
traditional Chinese painting.
</P>
<P>
In 1984 he was awarded a French literary and artistic honor and
likewise in 1986 received recognition by Belgian royalty.
</P>
<P>
The 13-day exhibition has been jointly organized by the Central
Academy of Fine Arts, the Chinese Artists' Association, the China
Art Gallery and the Wu Zuoren International Fine Arts Foundation.
</P>
</TEXT>
