<HEADLINE> China Celebrates Fifth Anniversary of Connection to Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The fifth anniversary of China's
computer networks connecting to the Internet was celebrated by the
Chinese Academy of Sciences here today.
</P>
<P>
Lu Yongxiang, the Academy's president, said that the Internet
in China has witnessed rapid growth since an education and
research network in Beijing was connected to the Internet in 1994,
with several computer networks, including the largest CHINANET,
established.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that nearly 750,000 computers in China
have been connected to the Internet and the number of users is now
2.1 million.
</P>
<P>
Lu said that China's connection to the Internet has promoted
the computer network construction in many sectors, which is a
great help to the country's national economic growth and social
development.
</P>
<P>
Surveys show that China saves several hundred million yuan
every year through organizing international academic conferences
and launching international cooperation projects on the Internet.
