<HEADLINE> Philippines' Tourism to Create 3.71 million Jobs by 2007 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' tourism industry
could be developed into a "great and reliable employment source"
and could absorb up to 3.71 million workers by 2007, a report of
the country's House of Representatives said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Department of Tourism sources as saying that
the country expects a movement of 16.204 million among domestic
tourists, who would spend about 53.47 billion pesos (about 1.3
billion U.S. dollars) by 2007.
</P>
<P>
"With the Philippines targeting visitor receipts of about 3.82
billion U.S. dollars from foreign arrivals of about 2.74 million,
this is definitely good news for the country," the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the prospects are based on several
global factors, including increasing long-haul travel, global
liberalization in tourism services, emergence of multilateral
aviation regime, growing middle-class and well-educated travel
groups, and advancements in information technology.
</P>
<P>
Also, recognition of travel and tourism as a basic human need,
increasing decision-making among women, and greater demand for
family-oriented travel will contribute to increased tourism
activity, the report said. 
</P>
