<HEADLINE> CCB to Grant 1999 Housing Loans Totaling 40 BLN Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank (CCB)
announced today that it will grant loans totaling 40 billion yuan
to the nation's housing sector this year.
</P>
<P>
A CCB spokesman said a major portion of the loans will be
earmarked for the housing consumption sector, with individuals
receiving some 30 billion yuan for housing purchases.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that the CCB's outstanding real estate
loans hit 261.7 billion yuan by the end of 1998, with the figure
for individual housing loans totaling 69.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
New individual housing loans accounted for 10.4 percent of the
increase in the bank's total loans.
</P>
<P>
The CCB's real estate loan target for this year focuses on
satisfying market demand while minimizing risks. Priority will be
placed on individual housing mortgage loans, the development of
profitable real estate projects and low-cost residential housing.
</P>
<P>
The CCB will make further efforts to improve service for
housing loans, according to the spokesman.  
</P>
