<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Development Zones Enjoys Preferential Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Economic and
Technological Development Zone (BETDZ) enjoys the same
preferential policies as state-level new and high technology
development zones.
</P>
<P>
Domestic enterprises engaged in high and new technology
development also benefit from preferential policies which include
15 percent income tax reduction, tax exemptions for the first two
years of operation following the acquisition of business licenses,
and a 50 percent tax reduction for the following three years.
Related preferential policies were previously restricted to
overseas-funded and export-oriented enterprises located in the
zone.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that the new preferential policies
attracted 44 new enterprises to the zone in the first quarter of
this year, a 4.5-fold rise on the previous year's period. Total
added investments during the period grew by 1.7-fold to 68 million
yuan (about 8.2 million U.S. dollars). Eleven of the new overseas-
funded enterprises involved cumulative investments of 56.81
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
A further analysis shows that world-famous overseas
corporations accounted for the bulk of new arrivals. Total
combined investments from the German-based Hoechst Group, which
focuses on pharmaceuticals and chemicals, and the Tontrush Group
approached 29 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some 30-odd multinational corporations, including SMC,
Panasonic and Shiseido from Japan, Swiss-based ABB, Bayer and
Henkel from Germany, Britain's Unilever, U.S.-based Lucent, Coca
Cola and McDonald's, accounted for over 60 percent of total
investments in place by the end of March.
</P>
<P>
Zone officials disclosed that plans for this year call for the
zone's sales volume to hit five billion yuan, with the fiscal
income expected to rise to 500 million yuan and export value to 80
million U.S. dollars. Growth rates for the respective areas are
expected to hover between 20-40 percent.
</P>
<P>
The development zone, founded in 1992, has played an important
role in the city's economic development. The BETDZ is currently
home to 338 enterprises with total investment of 1.72 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Growth rates for the zone's sales volume, fiscal income and
industrial output value during the first quarter of the year
surpassed 50 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
