Defense Minister Max Bradford are monitoring the growing crisis in
East Timor. He himself expects to visit Jakarta early next month
to express New Zealand's concerns about events in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Since violence began recently in East Timor, the New Zealand
Government has urged Indonesia to disarm the paramilitary groups
and hoped that the U.N.-sponsored talks between Portugal,
Indonesia and East Timorese leaders on Thursday will make
progress. 
