<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Continues to Attract Private Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- A total of 5,447 private
enterprises were established in Beijing in the first quarter of
this year, up 35.4 percent on the 1998 period, according to
statistics released by the Beijing Municipal Bureau for Industry
and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The 62,854 private enterprises in the Chinese capital have
total capital of 39.2 billion yuan (4.7 billion US dollars),
respective rises of 38.41 percent and 44.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Individuals set up approximately 5,200 enterprises, or 95
percent of the total for the first quarter. Some 54,780 individual
enterprises have total capital of 37.68 billion yuan, some 96
percent of the total capital for private enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Two hundred and seventy-six private enterprises in the
agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry and fisheries sectors have
enjoyed the most rapid development. Enterprises with the service
industry continue to hold dominant position, with some 52,260
related ventures accounting for 83 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Officials attribute the rapid development of private
enterprises to the capital's preferential policies and good
environment for growth. Various enterprises have enjoyed even
greater opportunities for further development after receiving
authorization to deal directly in exports and imports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
