<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Political Settlement of Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua)-- Chinese government calls for
immediate halt of military action so as to bring the settlement of
Kosovo crisis back to the track of political settlement, Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Sun Yuxi said here Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"If NATO sends ground forces to Yugoslavia, it will make the
regional situation deteriorated and more complicated," said the
spokesman in reply to a question at a routine press conference.
</P>
<P>
Since air strike against Yugoslavia began about four weeks ago,
Chinese government has for many times called on NATO to stop
military action and seek political solution of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin has reiterated on four occasions
the stand of the Chinese government, which is quite unprecedented.
In his oral message to Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic and
his letter in reply to U.S. President Bill Clinton, Jiang stressed
that China opposes the random use of force or the threat of use of
force by dint of military advantage.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the Kosovo issue should be solved fairly and
reasonably through negotiations under the prerequisite that the
sovereignty and territorial integrity of Yugoslavia should be
respected, and legitimate rights and interests of all ethnic
groups in Kosovo guaranteed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
