<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- NATO Secretary General Javier Solana announced on Monday
that the Apache "tank killers" will come into action next week.
This could mark a qualitative jump in the NATO engagement against
Yugoslavia. The U.S. sophisticated helicopters will let NATO
forces get closer to the ground instead of staying at high
altitude during bombing operations.
</P>
<P>
-- A column of vehicles, apparently civilian, from 20 to 25
kilometers long, is moving near Pristina and heading toward
southern Kosovo. About 850,000 people are displaced or considered
in danger inside Kosovo, according to NATO.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The flow of Kosovo Albanians seeking refuge in Albania or
Macedonia stopped on Monday, after the cutting of diplomatic
relations between Belgrade and Tirana and the closure of borders.
This has caused new worries about the fate of thousands of people.
</P>
