<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Zhu's Visit to Canada Successful: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua)-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji's
current official visit to Canada has scored "positive achievements,
" Foreign Ministry Spokesman Sun Yuxi said at a routine press
conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that Premier Zhu paid an official visit to Canada from
April 14 to 20 at the invitation of Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien. It is the first official visit to Canada paid by Zhu in
his capacity of premier and also a return visit for Chretien's
China tour last year.
</P>
<P>
Sun said, Premier Zhu and Canadian officials including Chretien
held frank, friendly and constructive talks on Sino-Canadian
relationship and regional and international issues of common
concern. Zhu has widely contacted and exchanged views with
Canadian personages of various circles.
</P>
<P>
Sun noted that the two sides have issued a joint communique on
bilateral negotiations for China's entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO) and affirmed the progress on this issue. The
two sides have also expressed determination to make more efforts
for reaching an agreement on this issue as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The visit, Sun noted, has deepened mutual understanding,
widened the common grounds, improved friendship and cooperation
between China and Canada, and also has further promoted the Sino-
Canadian comprehensive and cooperative partnership oriented to the
21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
