<HEADLINE> COMESA Moves to Ensure Product Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) will start implementing a project on
standardization, quality assurance, metrology and testing next
month now that the funds have been secured.
</P>
<P>
Financial Mail weekly Tuesday quoted COMESA Secretary General
Erastus Mwencha as saying that they have put everything in place
and the European Union has put in about 2.3 million U.S. dollars
for the region.
</P>
<P>
He said the project consists of a regional as well as a
national component but could not elaborate on how the two are
going to operate.
</P>
<P>
The money is intended to help member countries develop
standards, disseminate information to industries as well as assist
industries in training.
</P>
<P>
Mwencha said industry is of critical importance in revitalizing
 economies in the region and the integration of African economies
in the global economy.
</P>
<P>
Given the globalization of trade inherent in the current world
order, it is important for the countries in the region to not only
increase their supply of goods but improve the quality of the
products, said the COMESA chief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
