<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on Anti-China Speech by Japanese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that the Japanese
side would strictly observe the principles set in the Sino-
Japanese Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Treaty on Peace and
Friendship and ensure the relations between China and Japan to
develop in a healthy way.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi made remarks at a
routine press conference here today in reply to a reporter's
question.
</P>
<P>
He said that Tokyo and Beijing are friendship cities, and China
hopes that the two cities would maintain their friendly exchanges
and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"The erroneous remarks by an individual are unpopular and will
surely meet the opposition from the peoples in both China and
Japan," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The newly elected Governor of Metropolitan Tokyo Ishihara
Shintaro made an anti-China speech recently, which, according to
Sun, has hurted the feelings of the Chinese people and has done
harm to the Sino-Japanese ties and China has expressed its
indignation.  
</P>
