<HEADLINE> PBEC Annual Meeting to Be Held in HK in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The 32nd annual International
General Meeting (IGM) of the Pacific Basin Economic Council (PBEC)
will be held in Hong Kong from May 14-19.
</P>
<P>
Philippine President Joseph Estrada, Hong Kong SAR Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa, and Managing Director of the
International Monetary Fund Michel Camdessus will be among the
main speakers at the meeting, whose theme is "challenges of the
next century for the Pacific Basin."
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councilor Wu Yi, who just accompanied Chinese
Premier Zhu Rongji on a visit to the United States, will address
the opening gala dinner.
</P>
<P>
John Strickland, chairman of the IGM Steering Committee and the
Hong Kong Member Committee of PBEC, told a press conference
Tuesday this year's conference will take a forward-looking
approach and focus on the way ahead in the 21st century rather
than looking back at the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
There has already been much analysis of the causes of the
region's financial crisis and how countries and cities have been
affected in the last 21 months, he explained.
</P>
<P>
According to Douglas Fergusson, vice-chairman of the Hong Kong
Member Committee and president of Prudential Asia, said the
subjects of the meeting will include such important areas as
technology, communication, environment, trade barriers, and
electronic commerce.
</P>
<P>
The PBEC is an international association of senior business
leaders representing more than 1,100 major corporations in 20
economies around the Pacific. These corporations have a total
share of more than 4 trillion U.S. dollars in global sales and
employ more than 10 million people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
