<HEADLINE> Asia Pacific Leather Fair Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Asia Pacific Leather Fair
99 including two consecutive events opened at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The four-day raw materials and manufacturing show and the April
27-29 spring fashion and finished products show have gained
enthusiastic support from a total of over 3,500 exhibitors from
more than 60 countries and regions and participation from the key
industry associations.
</P>
<P>
The raw materials and manufacturing show, covering a total
floor space of 49,600 square meters, has drawn 2,629 exhibitors
from 64 countries and regions, who are presenting their latest
technology advancement and raw materials.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming spring show on the fashion and finished products
will feature the stylish and fashionable designs in footwear and
leather goods for the new season.
</P>
<P>
Michael Duck, general manager of Asia Pacific Leather Fair Ltd.,
said: "Moving into the new millennium, the industry faces new
challenges as new opportunities arise."
</P>
<P>
"The Asia Pacific Leather Fair will continue to work with the
industry into the new era by providing the most effective meeting
place and marketing tool for best business and hopefully a more
stable and profitable future," Duck added.
</P>
<P>
Turkey, the focus country of the Asia Pacific Leather fair,
features the country's major tanners with their quality raw
leathers.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Hide and Leather Traders Association has for the
first time organized its own pavilion, bringing small and medium-
sized companies to the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the value of Hong Kong's exports of leather
consumer goods in the first three months of last year amounted to
7.905 billion HK dollars (1.013 billion U.S. dollars), a 23
percent fall over the same period of 1997 mainly due to an overall
slowdown in the world's leather consumption. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
