<HEADLINE> Improved Beijing Environment Attracts Birds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the Chinese capital, is
home to 256 species of birds, including 58 species under State
protection.
</P>
<P>
The city had only 136 species of birds in 1990. Wang Zengnian,
an expert with the Beijing Wildlife Protection Center, attributed
the increase to the capital's efforts to increase general public
awareness of the need for protecting birds and the large-scale
afforestation drive carried out over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
The capital's forest coverage hit 41.22 percent by the end of
1998, with the per capita share of greenery standing at 8.18
square meters. 
</P>
