tribute to Dubai's attractions as an incentive travel destination
and business meeting venue," said Khalid bin Sulayem,
director-general of Dubai Department of Tourism and Commerce
Marketing.
</P>
<P>
"The results of this survey show that Dubai has the facilities
and services to compete with the best in the world," he added .
</P>
<P>
The survey highlighted Dubai's top class hotels, bargain
shopping and pleasant atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Other popular destinations that come close in the survey
include Naples, Jordan, Prague, Morocco, Hong Kong, Thailand, New
York and Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
