<HEADLINE> China Increases Funding for Technology Upgrades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua)-- China allocated some 33.07 billion
yuan (3.98 billion US dollars) for technology upgrades in the
first quarter of the year, up 13.7 percent on the 1998 period,
according to today's People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
This year's plan calls for related funding of some 470 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Daily quoted officials from the State Economic and Trade
Commission as saying that the government will no longer approve
loans for new industrial construction projects, with the exception
of projects involving high technology and good market potential.
</P>
<P>
The major portion of funding will be channeled to upgrading
existing state-owned enterprises (SOEs) in order to renovate the
country's industries and restructure the economy. Profitable SOEs
and ongoing construction projects, especially projects scheduled
for completion this year, will enjoy priority in terms of
investments.
</P>
<P>
The majority of investments will be earmarked for the
development of products with potentially large markets and high
competitiveness on the international market, according to the
Daily.  
</P>
</TEXT>
