<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE to Build Airport in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Unite Arab Emirates (UAE)
will build an international airport in Kokus, Albania, to
facilitate provision of relief and humanitarian aid to the Kosovo
refugees.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the airport was ordered by the UAE
President Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan, the Gulf News daily
reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project will start within two days and
will take 27 days to complete.
</P>
<P>
An old unused runway will be renovated to receive heavy
planes, said Fares Al Mazroui, the head of the UAE mission in
Tirana, Albania. He added cargo facilities for unloading aid
consignments will also be built.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the project will be announced at a later
time through an international tender, he added.
</P>
<P>
The UAE has sent a huge amount of relief materials to Tirana
since the Kosovo refugee crisis broke out in late March, when
NATO launched air strikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, more than 600,000 Ethnic Albanians, most of them
muslims, have fled Kosovo, a province of the Serbian Republic of
Yugoslavia, because of the war waged by separatists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
