<HEADLINE> China Records Rising Revenues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China collected 232.43 billion
yuan (28 billion US dollars) in revenue during the first three
months of the year, a year-on-year rise of 26.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Xinli, spokesperson for the State Development Planning
Commission, spoke at today's news conference sponsored by the
Information Office of the State Council and noted that the
increase was 17.4 percentage points higher than that in last
year's same period.
</P>
<P>
China's stable monetary policies prompted banks nationwide to
increase various types of loans by 143.7 billion yuan during the
first quarter of the year, up 52.3 billion yuan on the previous
year's period, according to Zheng.  
</P>
