<HEADLINE> British Arrested for Possessing Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot police detained a
British tourist suspected of possessing drugs, the Cyprus Mail
newspaper reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Karl Joseph Westwood, 39, was arrested on Monday by Cypriot
drug squad officers at a pub in Ayia Napa town, eastern Cyprus,
following a tip-off.
</P>
<P>
The police said Westwood was seen trying to swallow a piece of
hashish when they entered the pub. When policemen tried to step
in, Westwood allegedly insulted them.
</P>
<P>
And Westwood sustained head injuries during a tussle with the
policemen and the hash was removed from inside his mouth, police
said.
</P>
<P>
The police found 17.5 grams of hash in Westwood's holiday flat
at a hotel. 
</P>
