<HEADLINE> Norway Desires Constructive Dialog with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Former Norwegian Prime Minister
Thorbjoern Jagland said here today that Norway hopes to engaged in
mutually beneficial constructive dialog with China.
</P>
<P>
Jagland presented a speech entitled "Modern Social Democracy"
to Chinese scholars and noted the fruitful cooperation between the
two countries in recent years.
</P>
<P>
"Wide-ranging cooperation between the two countries has covered
everything from contacts at the highest political level to
cooperation and exchange of expertise between organizations,
companies and individuals," said Jagland, chairman of the
Norwegian Labor Party.
</P>
<P>
He added that cooperation has also covered the education of
judges, gender equality and the relations between both state and
non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
Jagland pointed to China's great social and economic progress,
as well as major challenges, and stressed that the nation's
participation in the World Trade Organization (WTO) will be an
important step in the right direction.  
</P>
