<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina Issues Bonds in Euros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 19 (Xinhua)-- Argentine Economic Ministry
on Monday issued credit bonds for 250 million euros, equivalent
to 266.1 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The bond which expires on March 18, 2004, has a yield of 8.11
percent in euros, which is equivalent to 10.46 percent in dollars,
with a rate of 10.5 per cent until March 18, year 2000 and seven
per cent after that.
</P>
<P>
The bond will be exchangeable after March 18, year 2000 with a
previous placing in Italian lira of the same date of expiry, said
the Economic Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The bond, which shall be set by British legislation, will be
totally redeemed at expiry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
