<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Raptors Stun East-Leading Magic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Toronto Raptors outwitted
the Orlando Magic 90-72 on Monday, hoping to make the playoff for
the first time in the National Basketball Association.
</P>
<P>
Magic, the leaders in the Eastern Conference, were confined to
nine points in the second quarter and 14 in the third, and their
72 points became the defensive records for the young Toronto
franchise.
</P>
<P>
Tracy McGrady scored 12 of 16 points in the fourth quarter,
Kevin Willis also had 16 points, and Vince Carter 14.
</P>
<P>
The Raptors (20-20) thus tied New York (21-21) and Charlotte (
20-20) for ninth place in the Eastern Conference, one-half game
behind Cleveland for the final playoff slot in the East.
</P>
<P>
The Magic (29-13) had lost three of its last four games after a
six-game winning streak, but still lead Miami (27-13) by one game
in the Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
In Cleveland, Dan Majerle scored a season-high 22 points as the
Miami Heat moved closer to the top spot in the Eastern Conference
standings with a 94-87 victory over the Cavaliers as it has won
eight of its last 10 games.
</P>
<P>
In New Jersey, veteran Chuck Person came off the bench to drain
three crucial 3-pointers as the Charlotte Hornets extended their
season-high winning streak to eight with a 120-113 over the Nets.
</P>
<P>
In Philadelphia, Patrick Ewing missed a jumper with 23 seconds
left, giving the 76ers a 72-67 victory over the Knicks which has
lost a season-high four straight.
</P>
<P>
In Boston, Reggie Miller scored 23 points as the Indiana rolled
to a 120-104 victory over the Celtics, snapping a two-game losing
skid and pulling within two games of Orlando for the Eastern
Conference lead.
</P>
<P>
In Houston, Charles Barkley's free throw, and Sam Mack's
seventh 3-pointer just 26 seconds later broke open a close game
which the Rockets eventually won 120-113 over the Seattle
SuperSonics.
</P>
<P>
Mack scored 21 points off the bench, all on 3-pointers as he
shot 7-of-11 from behind the arc.
</P>
<P>
In Anaheim, rookie Jason Williams scored 19 points and a season-
high 14 assists as the Sacramento Kings rallied for a 102-98
victory over the Los Angeles Clippers, as the Kings (19-22) moved
into a tie with Seattle for the final playoff spot in the Western
Conference.
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Lakers snapped a three-game losing streak with
a 117-102 victory over the lowly Vancouver Grizzlies as Shaquille
O'Neal scored 31 points, but the Lakers still remained 1 1/2 games
behind Houston for fourth place in the Western Conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
