<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Spends 8 Billion Yuan for Rail Construction in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China poured eight billion yuan
into railway construction in the first quarter this year,
according to the Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
During this period, some 224.2 kilometers of new railway lines
were built and 152.4 kilometers of double-tracks were completed,
accounting for 17 percent and 15.6 percent of the plan for the
year, respectively.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, some 173.5 kilometers of the double-track
lines were put into operation.
</P>
<P>
China plans to spend at least 55 billion yuan to build 1,320
kilometers of new rail lines, 970 kilometers of double-tracks, and
730 kilometers of electrified railways this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
