<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier: Canada Visit Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VICTORIA, Canada, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu
Rongji said his seven-day official visit to Canada has achieved
the goal of deepening understanding, expanding common ground,
enhancing friendship and promoting cooperation between China and
Canada.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks at a dinner here Monday night jointly held
by Canadian Minister of Fisheries and Oceans David Anderson and
Secretary of State for Asia-Pacific Affairs Raymond Chan.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Premier said he came to Canada to follow out the
common ground reached by Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien during Jiang's state visit
to Canada in 1997 so as to advance the 21st century-oriented China-
Canada partnership of all-round cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"We have made utmost efforts, and the visit of the Chinese
government delegation to Canada is successful," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu arrived in St. John's, capital of Canada's Newfoundland
province, on April 14 following his successful eight-day visit to
the United States.
</P>
<P>
He said he is convinced that the China-Canada friendly
cooperation will be further enhanced through the visit of the
Chinese delegation led by him.
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed his heartfelt thanks to the Canadian government
and people for their welcome and hospitality accorded to the
Chinese delegation.
</P>
<P>
In their speeches, both Anderson and Chan said the maintenance
of the close cooperation between Canada and China is important and
expressed the hope that the two countries will strengthen their
existing friendly and cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Premier of British Columbia Glen Clark hosted a
luncheon in honor of Premier Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Zhu will leave here for Vancouver, the last stop of his ongoing
trip, Tuesday morning and return home in the afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
