<HEADLINE> Three Foreign Journalists Killed in Albanian Car Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Three foreign journalists and
their Albanian driver were killed Sunday after the car they were
riding fell into a ravine in northern Albania, an Albanian
newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report said an American couple and a French woman were
killed in the accident caused by a hail storm around noon near the
town of Tuka in northern Albania.
</P>
<P>
They were on their way back to Tirana after a visit to refugee
camps in the city of Kukesi bordering Yugoslavia's Kosovo province.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 130,000 Kosovo refugees have gathered in Kukesi since
NATO began bombing Yugoslavia late last month. Many robberies
targeting foreign journalists have reportedly happened in the city.
