<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Issue Industrial Bond in Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will launch an
industrial development bond in Britain this month to raise money
for the country's industrial development.
</P>
<P>
The bond will formally introduced on April 22 by Finance
Minister Shah A.M.S. Kibria, who is now in Paris at a two-day
meeting of Bangladesh Aid Consortium, The Independent newspaper
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government is looking forward to raising 100 million U.S.
dollars by selling the bond, which would be in dollars, and
investors would get an interest rate of 8.6 percent and have the
opportunity of drawing both the interest and the principal in
dollars.
</P>
<P>
It might take several months to release the bond that is
targeted primarily at Bangladeshis living in the Middle East and
in other countries, said Golam Rahman, additional secretary of the
Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The bond is intended to encourage Bangladeshi expatriates to
make investment by guaranteeing them the benefits that accrue due
to change in the exchange rates of hard currencies form time to
time, he said.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Bangladesh sought 2.04 billion dollars in foreign
aid at the Paris meeting which would end on Tuesday, but the
country's donors earlier had announced that they would not make
aid pledges at the meeting this year. 
</P>
