opposition party, called on the country to avoid involvement in
NATO strikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Nicolae Vacaroiu, the party's deputy chief, said Romania has
already signed peace agreements with Yugoslavia, and the bilateral
relations have always been harmonious. 
