<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Calls for Return of Kosovo Issue to Political Means </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Monday emphasized that the halt of NATO airstrikes against
Yugoslavia is a necessary precondition for solving the Kosovo
crisis, according to the Russian Presidential Press Office.
</P>
<P>
During a 50-minute telephone conversation with his U.S.
counterpart Bill Clinton, Yeltsin called for urgent measures to
take the problem back to the political track.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin also urged implementation of the basic principles
agreed upon during a recent meeting between Russian foreign
minister and the U.S. secretary of state in Oslo, which, he
believed, would help reverse the worse-going Kosovo situation.
</P>
<P>
During the Oslo meeting, according to Yeltsin, the two sides
agreed to resume negotiations on the framework of granting Kosovo
extensive self-governing rights based on the precondition of
complete respect of Yugoslavia's sovereignty and territorial
integrity.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents also discussed the returning of ethnic
Albanian and Serbian refugees. Yeltsin stressed the necessity of
the participation by Yugoslav leaders in solving this problem
under the supervision of the international community. 
</P>
