<HEADLINE> Tianjin Port Increases First Quarter Cargo Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin Port, the largest
facility of its kind in north China, handled 17.4 million tons of
import and export goods in the first quarter of this year, a year-
on-year rise of 7.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The import volume grew 28.7 percent to 3.46 million tons, with
the export volume falling by 6.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Increasing domestic trade has sparked an increase in the port's
import volume. However, the adverse impact of the Asian financial
crisis has led to a simultaneous decline in exports.
</P>
<P>
The port's internal trade goods for the first quarter hit 8.1
million tons, up 28 percent from the previous year's period.
</P>
