<HEADLINE> China's Agriculture Up Four Percent in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China's agricultural sector had a
four-percent year-on-year increase in the first quarter of the
year, National Bureau of Statistics Spokesman Ye Zhen said here
today.
</P>
<P>
According to a sample survey, the bureau expects the total area
sown to crops this year to reach 2.34 billion mu (156 million
hectares).
</P>
<P>
This represents an increase of 13.5 million mu (900,000
hectares) from last year's figure, including 525,000 mu (35,000
hectares) designated for grains, the spokesman told a press
conference here.
</P>
<P>
Ye said material supplies for the spring ploughing are
sufficient, and are better prepared than last year.
</P>
<P>
An investigation into the supply and demand of 13 major
materials needed for the spring ploughing in more than 800
counties across the country shows that the supply of 11 materials
is up to 95 percent of the demand.
</P>
<P>
Pesticides, seeds and large and medium-sized farm tools are
adequately provided, Ye added.  
</P>
