<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added China's Economy Grows 8.3 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China's economic growth remained
in a fast track to reach 8.3 percent in the first quarter of this
year, the National Bureau of Statistics said here today.
</P>
<P>
Gross domestic product (GDP) totaled 1.6784 trillion yuan
during the period, spokesman Ye Zhen of the bureau told a press
conference.
</P>
<P>
"As the state's policy of increasing investment and stimulating
domestic demand keeps to take effect, the national economy has
maintained a favorable momentum," Ye said.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector registered a growth rate of four
percent in the first three months of this year, while the
industrial sector grew 9.7 percent and the tertiary sector seven
percent.
</P>
<P>
Deflationary trend continued during the period, with the retail
price index declining 2.9 percent year-on-year and the consumer
price index dropping 1.4 percent, the spokesman said.  
</P>
