<HEADLINE> China Opens First Asset Management Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China's first asset management
company, which copes with non-performing loans of banks, opened
here today.
</P>
<P>
The Cinda Asset Management Corporation, with a total registered
capital of 10 billion yuan, will mainly focus its business on
managing non-performing loans and assets transferred from banks.
</P>
<P>
Cinda is an independent state-owned financial institution under
the supervision of the People's Bank of China, the country's
central bank. It also has access to trusting business for other
financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The 10-billion-yuan capital will be allocated by the Ministry
of Finance, officials said at a press conference held here today
by the State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
President and vice-president will be appointed by the State
Council. 
</P>
