<HEADLINE> Fixed Asset Investment Grows Rapidly In First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China's fixed assets investment,
excluding that by collectively-owned and private enterprises,
increased 22.7 percent in the first quarter this year over the
same period last year to 202.3 billion yuan, with the growth rate
going up 12.4 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, investment in infrastructure construction jumped
28.1 percent to 117.9 billion yuan, said Ye Zhen, spokesman with
the National Bureau of Statistics, at a press conference here
today.
</P>
<P>
Investment in renovation increased 13.7 percent to 33.1 billion
yuan, while real estate investment surged 19.4 percent to 41.3
billion yuan and investment in other sectors rose 9.7 percent to
10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investment continued to focus on basic industries and
infrastructure construction. Investment in the sectors of
agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry, fishery and water
conservancy jumped 122.1 percent to 8.1 billion yuan, accounting
for 4 percent of the total investment as compared with 2.2 percent
in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in transportation and post and telecommunications
surged 46 percent to 43 billion yuan, accounting for 21.3 percent
of the total investment, up 3.4 percentage points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
