<HEADLINE> Chinese People Have More to Spend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese urban residents had a per
capita disposable income of 1,632 yuan in the first quarter of the
year, 6.4 percent more than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
When the price drop factor is taken into account, the increase
stands at eight percent in real terms, which is 2.8 percentage
points higher than a year earlier, National Bureau of Statistics
Spokesman Ye Zhen told a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that rural residents had a per capita cash
income of 587 yuan in the three months, up 3.1 percent on an
annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The real growth in the per capita cash income of rural
residents is 5.2 percent, three percentage points higher than the
same period last year.  
</P>
