<HEADLINE> Modern Dance Drama Portrays Life in Shenzhen Special Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- A modern dance drama entitled
Shenzhen Story will be staged in Beijing from April 22-25 to mark
the 50th founding anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen was China's first Special Economic Zone after the
introduction of the country's reform and opening up policy, as the
setting of the story. The dance tells the story of three girls who
come to the city seeking the land of promise.
</P>
<P>
Their growing into maturity, life setbacks, and continuous
struggle for a better future are expressed in an unique artistic
way through dance.
</P>
<P>
According to the director Ying Eding, the script was rewritten
three times and the play had its debut in Shenzhen last December.
</P>
<P>
In order to portray this vivid dimension of modern life of
Shenzhen, the cast frequently visited real-life young fortune-
seekers and asked them to watch the show's rehearsals and offer
their opinions.  
