<HEADLINE> Suns Jason Kidd Named NBA Player of the Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Phoenix Suns guard Jason Kidd,
who led his team to three wins in four games with his stellar all-
around play, today was named NBA Player of the Week for the period
ending Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kidd averaged 22.8 points, 10.5 assits, 5.0 rebounds and 2.75
steals in four games. He shot 48 percent from the field and made
all 18 free throws as Phoenix improved to 21-20, good for seventh
place in the Western Conference.
</P>
<P>
Kidd did not add to his league-leading triple-double total of
five, but came close on two occations. He had 22 points, nine
rebounds, nine assists and four steals in a 94-77 loss at San
Antonio last Monday and collected 30 points, 10 assists and six
rebounds in Wednesday's 101-94 win over Seattle.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Kidd had 24 points and 12 assists in a 92-85 victory
over Dallas and two days later totaled 15 points and 11 assists,
giveing Phoenix its first season series sweep of the Pacific
Division rival SuperSonics.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates included forwars Antonio McDyess and Danny
Fortson of Denver, Chris Webber of Sacramento and Shawn Kemp of
cleveland. 
