<HEADLINE> China Develops First Inter-City Electricity-Powered Locomotive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China has developed its first
electricity-powered train for inter-city or downtown suburban
transport, which can reach an average speed of 120 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
The train was jointly developed by the Changchun Passenger Car
Plant, the Kunming Railroad Administration Bureau and the Zhuzhou
Electricity-Powered Locomotive Research Institute.
</P>
<P>
Electricity-powered locomotives are considered safe, convenient,
pollution-free, and ideal for shuttling between cities and between
downtown and suburban areas.
</P>
<P>
The first train of the type, named "Spring City", has finished
trials at a railway test center in Beijing. The first train for
commercial use will travel between Kunming City, southwest Yunnan
Province, and the nearby stone forest during the '99 Kunming
International Horticulture Exposition which begins on May 1st.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990420.0315 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' International Reserve Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The gross international reserve of
the Philippines has reached a record high of 13.2 billion U.S.
dollars in April, the country's central bank governor Gabriel
Singson said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Singson said in an interview that the reserve is beefed up by
the secondary reserve comprising foreign currency deposits at the
country's various banks.
</P>
<P>
This amount is still short of the reserve target of 15 billion
U.S. dollars for the full year set by the International Monetary
Fund, he said.
</P>
<P>
Singson said the increase in the reserve was the effect of the
good performance of the country's stock market whose shares of
stock are attracting foreign funds into the financial system.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the implementation of the government's
economic measures has resulted in the improvement of foreign
investors' trust in the country's financial system.
</P>
<P>
The government has put in place efficient monetary and fiscal
measures to caution the impact of crisis like massive outflow of
foreign funds due to unfavorable developments in the country, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
