<HEADLINE> Guilin Initiates Ecological Agricultural Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Guilin, a well-known scenic city
in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, recently
initiated an ecological agricultural program focusing on
intensified efforts to improve the environment and promote the
agriculture and forestry sectors.
</P>
<P>
Five counties, 20 townships, and 100 village have been
designated as pilot zones for establishing ecological agriculture
by the year 2003.
</P>
<P>
Hygienic and environmental conditions will improve greatly in
pilot localities over the next five years. Local authorities noted
that 50 percent of local households will use marsh gas for cooking,
and solar energy will be used for more farm projects.
</P>
<P>
Farmers control cash forests covering an average of one mu (0.
067 hectares), with the annual per capita grain availability
rising to more than 420 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Tourism officials are confident the effort will attract more
visitors to the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
