<HEADLINE> France Sets Up Fund to Help Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 20 (Xinhua) -- France is offering a grant of 1.3
billion U.S. dollars to 10-15 Asian countries, including Thailand,
for development projects.
</P>
<P>
The message was conveyed to Sethaporn Kusripithak,
director-general of the Post and Telegraph Department of the Thai
government by visiting officials from the French Economics
Ministry Monday, the Bangkok Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
France has not set a specific amount for each country. The sum
will depend on proposals of fund receivers and the consideration
of France, Sethaporn was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The grant is aimed at funding feasibility studies, technology
transfers and technical assistance for development projects.
</P>
<P>
Along with the grant, France has also offered soft loans at a
1-percent interest rate to fund development projects in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Sethaporn said the grant would benefit Thailand. 
