<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Province Effectively Reduces Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The poverty-stricken population in
northwest China's Shaanxi Province has dropped by close to four
million people since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi had poverty-stricken population of over five million
prior to the Government's initiation of a massive poverty relief
program in 1993. The vast majority of the poverty-stricken
population lived in Qinling Mountain areas and dry plateaus.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has extended great effort to improve
local conditions for agricultural production and encourage local
farmers to develop fruit and breeding industries, with special
emphasis on the apple industry.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi has granted loans of over 570 million yuan since 1993
to help rural households develop agricultural and sideline
industries.
</P>
<P>
A total of 75,000 poverty-stricken people have migrated from
frigid mountain areas found at high elevations with
characteristically poor basic living conditions.
</P>
<P>
The local plan calls for helping an additional 700,000 people
escape poverty during 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
