<HEADLINE> Austrian Defense Chief Deems Kosovo Crisis Catastrophe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Defense Minister Werner
Fasslabend warned here Monday that the Kosovo crisis is the
biggest humanitarian and political catastrophe facing Europe ever
since World War Two.
</P>
<P>
To maintain order and stability in the Balkan region is vital
to peripheral countries, and Austria vows to seek a peaceful
solution to the Kosovo crisis, Fasslabend told the press after
meeting with his Hungarian counterpart Szabo Janos.
</P>
<P>
The debate in Austria on whether to join the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO) should be brought to a halt, because
the country's security policy should not be the main topic of the
general elections, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fasslabend was on a one-day visit to Hungary for discussions
with Hungarian leaders about bilateral relations and the Kosovo
crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
