<HEADLINE> Wuhan to Reinforce Yangtze Embankments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Wuhan, capital city of central
China's Hubei Province, plans to invest 1.07 billion yuan over the
next three years to reinforce embankments along the Yangtze and
Hanjiang rivers.
</P>
<P>
The embankments stretch 465 kilometers. Workers will move
nearly 50 million cu. m. of dirt and stone to expand the width of
the embankments to eight meters.
</P>
<P>
The embankments will be able to withstand the volume of massive
flooding experienced in 1954, according to local authorities who
pledged to ensure the high quality of the project. 
</P>
