<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wise Escapes UEFA Suspension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- England Premier League soccer club
Chelsea skipper escaped suspension when UEFA gave his green light
to play against Mallorca in the second leg of the European Cup
Winners' Cup semifinals on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The UEFA disciplinary committee in Geneva dismissed the case
against Wise who had been accused of biting Mallorca's Marcelino
in the shoulder during the first leg at Stamford Bridge two weeks
ago.
</P>
<P>
It decided that although Wise's "unsporting gesture warrants
clear disapproval, there is no legal basis in UEFA's disciplinary
regulations for imposing a disciplinary sanction".
</P>
<P>
Dick Jol, the Dutch referee, did not book the midfielder for
the incident which was caught by television cameras.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, UEFA said that Wise appeared to make an attempt
to bite Marcelino after a goalmouth incident.
</P>
<P>
UEFA confirmed on Monday they can impose sanctions for
incidents not seen by the referee if such incidents correspond to
"gross unsportsmanship".
</P>
<P>
UEFA said: "The incident must be so serious that failing to
punish it would contradict general legal opinion."
</P>
<P>
But the committee, chaired by Alain Courtois of Belgium,
dismissed the case.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea, the Cup Winners' Cup holders, were held to a 1-1 draw
by Mallorca in London. The second leg is in Spain on Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
