<HEADLINE> More Businesses to Help Fight Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China will encourage more
businesses to become involved in the management of pollution
control facilities.
</P>
<P>
Yin Gai, director of the technology and standards department of
the State Environmental Protection Administration (SEPA), said
that the administration will authorize a number of companies to
operate pollution control facilities.
</P>
<P>
With the country's enhanced environmental protection efforts,
many cities and enterprises have installed such facilities.
However, a large number have not operated well due to weak
environmental awareness, backward technology and poor management.
</P>
<P>
The SEPA selected 17 companies last December to run anti-
pollution programs on a trial basis and the companies will be
issued licenses in May if they are running well, said Yin who
attended a meeting here recently on the management of pollution
control facilities.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that detailed policies will be drafted to encourage
more companies to become involved. 
</P>
