<HEADLINE> BFU Bans Levski Kyustendil from Hosting Three Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 19 (Xinhua) - The Disciplinary Committee with the
Bulgarian Football Union (BFU) announced on Monday its decision to
ban Levski Kyustendil from hosting three matches and to impose 720,
000 leva (720 Deutsche marks) fine on the club.
</P>
<P>
The decision is in connection with an incident which took place
on April 11 during a 22nd round match between Levski Kyustendil
and CSKA, when two CSKA footballers, goalie Ivailo Ivanov and
defender Adalbert Zafirov, were beaten in the half time.
</P>
<P>
CSKA refused to take the field after the incident.
</P>
<P>
The BFU Technical Committee ruled that no points be awarded
from the match to any of the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Levski Kyustendil will deposit a complaint at the BFU
Appellative Commission against the decision of the Disciplinary
Committee, the club's Executive Director Emil Nakov said.
</P>
<P>
"We are the injured party and we will seek our rights. If the
Appellative Committee turns down our complaint, we will protest
before the BFU Executive Committee and even before UEFA and a
civil court," Nakov said. 
</P>
