<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arsenal Trounce Wimbledon 5-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Arsenal
narrowed its gap to one point with English Premier League
pacesetter Manchester United after a 5-1 win over Wimbledon on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ray Parlour slotted in the opener in the 34th minute but
Arsenal really ran wild in the second half.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Vieira made it 2-0 in the 49th minute with a left-
footed rocket from the edge of the area off a pass from Nigel
Winterburn and the floodgates were opened.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal scored three goals in a three minute spell, with
Wimbledon's Ben Thatcher making it 3-0 in the 56th after a header
from Nigerian Nwankwo Kanu rebounded off the upright and into the
path of the luckless defender.
</P>
<P>
Dennis Bergkamp, who floated in the ball for Kanu's header,
made it 4-0 in the 57th with a right-footed shot that goalkeeper
Neil Sullivan could only deflect in at the far post.
</P>
<P>
Kanu, robbed of one goal, then made sure of another by linking
up with Vieira and finishing a long-legged run into the box with a
toe-in on the line as Sullivan dived in vain.
</P>
<P>
Carl Cort pulled a goal back for Wimbledon in the 70th minute
with a header off a free kick but there were no celebrations from
a visiting team that was never in the match and could have gone
considerably further behind.
</P>
<P>
United, who now have a game in hand over Arsenal and who beat
the Londoners 2-1 in an epic F.A. Cup semifinal replay five days
ago, have 67 points while Arsenal have 66.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea, who have played the same number of games as Arsenal,
are third on 64.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal beat Wimbledon 5-0 a year ago in the match that sent
them a point clear of United and on the way to the title.
</P>
<P>
In Monday's clash, Arsenal scored the same number of goals but
were left one point short of their rivals. But, on this sort of
form, nobody will be counting them out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
