<HEADLINE> Beijing Families Keen to Install Second Telephone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 30,000 families in
Beijing have applied for an additional domestic telephone since
telecom authorities cut the fees on March 1st this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure is 232 percent of that for the same period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The cost of installing a first telephone in Beijing has been
lowered from 3,600 yuan (430 US dollars) to more than 1,000 yuan (
120 US dollars) as approved by the municipal government.
</P>
<P>
There is now no charge to install a second or additional phone
line in a single family, according to the regulation. This was
part of a Ministry of Information Industry plan to cut telephone
installation fees.
</P>
<P>
Many people joined a long line in front of the Beijing
Municipal Telephone Office to apply for telephone installation,
eyewitnesses said.
</P>
<P>
And about 100,000 Beijingers have submitted applications since
March 1. More than 60,000 of them have had the telephones
installed including a second phone for 10,000 families.
</P>
<P>
There are now an average of 48 telephones for every 100
residents in the Chinese capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
