<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 20 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and eight
other injured in civilian buidlings in Nis, 220 kilometers
southeast of Belgrade, in an NATO air raid late Monday, Serbia's
RTS television reported.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav Tanjug news agency said at least seven bombs or
missiles hit northwestern districts of Nis in a 20-minute raid
from 11:00 p.m. (2100 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Housing in Bujmirska Street, near the Crveni Krst railway
station, was struck, as well as a building firm, in the seventh
attack on Nis since the NATO air strikes against Yugoslavia began
on March 24, Tanjug said.
</P>
<P>
The district also includes an industrial zone, the agency added.
