<HEADLINE> UNDP Marks 20th Anniversary of Aid to Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A week-long celebration to
mark the 20th anniversary of a United Nations Development Program
(UNDP) aid scheme to Palestinians ends on Tuesday in Gaza City, the
UNDP announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
UNDP has managed an annual 50 million U.S. dollars of
development projects for the Palestinian people since the U.N.
General Assembly adopted a relevant resolution in 1978.
</P>
<P>
The resolution called on UNDP to improve the economic and
social conditions of the Palestinian people by identifying their
needs and by establishing concrete projects.
</P>
<P>
UNDP has received donations to fund capacity-building projects
with the long-term goals of alleviating unemployment, creating
income-earning and educational opportunities for women, and
providing basic services to the poor among the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
In the past four years, UNDP has launched a total of 234
projects for the purpose. 
</P>
</TEXT>
