<HEADLINE> Dow Retreats After Big Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
retreated Monday as traders took profits after a big rise of the
index last week.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed down 53.36 at 10,440.53. At early Afternoon, the
index rose 271.85 to 10,765.74 before falling.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip stocks gained 320.05 points to reach the record
closing high of 10,493.89 in five trading days last week.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also lower. The technology heavy
Nasdaq index fell 138.43 to 2,345.61 in a continuation of last
week's downturn trend.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq was stunned again by the ousting of Compaq's chief
executive Eckhard Pfeiffer on Sunday. The computer maker rocked
the Wall Street earlier this month when it reported dismal
earnings projection.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was down 29.52 at 1,289.48
while The NYSE composite index was down 9.02 at 615.88.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange index fell 10.30 to 735.11 and the
Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 9.17 to 412.41.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered the decliners by 2-to-1 on the New
York Stock Exchange and NYSE volume increased to 1.2 billion
shares from 998 million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
